item.title: Water Temple SUCKS (Lynn Jr, Rigby, Quagsire, DP)
item.media:title: Water Temple SUCKS (Lynn Jr, Rigby, Quagsire, DP)
item.media:description:
Oh the Water Temple from The Legend Of Zelda: Ocarina Of Time, the one of most infamous level in all of Zelda, if not all of Video Games. Since it's OOT's birthday, I figured why not upload another artwork to celebrate it's 20th Anniversary, since my previous one just got favoured

This one consists the characters of Lynn Jr. (Loud House), Rigby (Regular Show), Quagsire (Pokemon), and Deadpool (Marvel), all going through the hell hole known as the water temple built by the Zoras, with them discussing their opinions. It'd probably go like this

Lynn Jr (Angry): I hate this stupid place, it's no fun. I'M LYNN JR, I'M NUMBER ONE!!!!!!! GRRRRRRRRR

Rigby (Bored): Dude, thatSo lame, (looks at Quagsire) can't believe you enjoyed it

Quagsire (Calm): QUUUAAAGSIIIREEE (IT wasn't that bad)

Rigby (Bored): That's because you have 3D Glasses

Deadpool (Freaking Out): OH GOD THIS IS WORSE THAN THAT TIME MARVEL BANNED US FROM THEIR CROSSOVER WITH CAPCOM 

I decided to add aura around Lynn, as if she had angry aura like what anime characters had in anime. I also decided to make Rigby look at Quagsire (who's wearing a headband), to make it seem like they are having a conversation. To make it seem like the Water Temple, I added dark link behind Deadpool, A Tektite and and Spike Ball trolling Lynn Jr, a Gold Skulltula, Iron boots Hovering Quagsire with a pause button if you know what I mean l, and finally for the finishing touch, the boss of the temple Morpha Giving the Finger to all of the characters. 

By the way did you catch that references in the picture? Trust me,  they're hilarious . 

All characters in this picture are owned by their respected owners.
Lynn Jr, Nickelodeon, Viacom
Rigby, Cartoon Network
Quagsire, Nintendo, The Pokemon Company
Deadpool, Marvel, 20th Century Fox
Dark Link, Morpha, Tektite, Spike Ball, Iron Boots, and Gold Skulltula, Nintendo 
Pause Button, No One

Anyway people, hope you guys have a great time, and I'll see you guys next time.

Happy 20th Anniversary Ocarina of Time

item.title: Call of Duty: True Capitalist Warfare
item.media:title: Call of Duty: True Capitalist Warfare
item.media:description:
Before you jumped the shark at me, this is a parody intention on True Capitalists Radio and the upcoming Call of Duty: Black Ops 4.

...Okay, you know what? This one deserve an attention.

When I heard the news that Call of Duty: Black Ops 4 becomes the Battle Royale game and the single-player campaign mode was (allegedly) removed before the reveal trailer, I've decided to draw this pic to poke fun at it.

This artwork is pretty much difficult to draw for me. Drawing troll faces from rage comics are okay but the background and pinpointing Austin, Texas from outer space on low orbit and the exact spot for the cover art are very challenging for me but I finally get the job done. During my work, I just laughed out loud myself when I look at it because it's funny.

This artwork was supposed to be for poking fun at Ghost, a radio show host from True Capitalist Radio before his last show ended this year, but I've decided to poke at both TCR and Call of Duty.

Though officially I'm not one of those guys from 4Chan, I'm just an artist who do some cool and crazy stuff around my work. Also, I've added Easter Eggs. Can you find them?

In case if you don't know who Ghost really is, then here's the link to proof it: truecapitalist.miraheze.org/wi…

Hope you like this one, fellas. Enjoy my artwork!


“Troll Warfare, Internet Warfare, Troll Ops, Rage Commandos, call it whatever you like. We love this idea and game. We do not forgive Activision but we do not forget this awesome game!”
-Anonymous

“Oh my, this game is totally legit!”
-Tub Guy

“What the fuck is this shit?!”
-Infinity Wards

“Troll Commandos in Space Marines uniforms?! Really??”
-Treyarch

We didn't made the game like this!
-Activision

“You sick twisted sonavabitch! You made a video game to poke a fun out of me to make me look like a freaking bad guy and make Capitalism look bad while you troll terrorist scumbags and cyber vermin assholes are bunch of heroes dressing up like a GODDAMN United States space marines to take me down in outer space like freaking Thanos from the Avengers movie and this is what I get a respect from you, you stupid little fu - *cans.wav* - That's it! Stick a fork at me-- I'm done! I'm done! Stick a fork at me, I'm Goddamn done!! I'm done with this crappy game!”
-Ghost, the True Capitalists Radio host

It is the year 2020 CE, two years after President Donald Trump died by a fatal heart attack by eating too much junk foods and our country was in a complete disarray and in great chaos until the True Capitalist Radio host, the man they called him “Ghost” suddenly became the President of the United States and changed the world what they should've done years ago forever. Now two years later, America has become known as the Greater Republic of Texas and it is a totalitarian far-right regime that brought them back to the dark age and the nightmare was realized from an iconic novel from Orson Welles’ “1984”. Their freedom of speech and expression was taken away from the people and the public medias, democrats and liberals were expelled, banned and crushed from politics, marshal law'd the entire system and social media, and invaded and conquered half of the world as we know it and transformed into a world of greedy intoxication of the reshaped Capitalism with Communism influential experimentations which they already knew it. Even worse, President Ghost have implemented microtransactions and loot boxes into law and everyone and I mean everybody must pay up their cash if they want go on with their daily lives as well to continue play the game and they're going to get away with it?!

Someone has to stop him and his brutal oppressive regime... Until now.

You are Private James Ramirez, a member of Rage Commandos, a squad of rag-tag freedom fighters from the old United States and the free world of the internet battle against the Capitalist Army on a global scale and liberate America from President Ghost and his Inner Circle before they will destroy us all.

* An All-New Single-Player Campaign Mission - Play as a member of Rage Commandos as you fight your way for freedom against the True Capitalist Regime in a full linear storyline, from the jungle warfare in Viet-f***ing-Nam to the war-torn nation of People's Republic of China to the heart of the American battlefield including Austin, the capital of the Greater Republic of Texas, to duke it out in outer space and on the moon so pack your bags and grab your guns, rookies! You’re gonna be Space Marines! Written by the Award-losing writers from Call of Duty: Ghost and Call of Duty: Infinite Warfare and inspired from Micheal Bay's patriotic movies like The Rock, Bad Boys 1 & 2, Pearl Harbor, 13 Hours, and the Transformers franchise.

* Classic Multiplayer Mode - Go head-2-head with your opponents in boots-to-the-ground classic, on solo or team deathmatch in a battleground like in the war-torn University of Texas, the defense of border wall between Mexico and Texas, the urban warfare in Shanghai, from Hue to Ho Chi Minh City in Vietnam, and fan-favorite map of Nuketown in Texas Style with a brand new Ninja Knifing/Punching Mode and no penalty problem at all with grieving and trolling funny stupid people and squeakers! Oh, we didn’t forget our classic Zombies Mode and the return of Aliens Mode where you fight off the invaders on your home planet or their home turf on Mars!

* Meet the Cast of Interesting Characters - Meet the friends and foes alike like iconic troll faces from Rage Comics and the folks from True Capitalist Regime's Inner Circle and Enemy's List like Vice-President Engineer, Tyrone, Mister Fortune Cookies, The Guru, Paco, Mahmoud/Machmoud, Alex Jones, Ghetto Capitalist, Tub Guy, Tri$ha, Asho, The Internet Buttstalker, Suck Mah D*** Guy, Xarahox the Piano Man, Tzeki, Coodoo17, GOOFY_BONE, The African Booty Scratcher, Teutonic Plague, bmar86, K-K-K-Keemstar from DramaAlert, The Brony Network and more to encounter during the gameplay! Including Call of Duty characters like Alex Mason, Frank Woods, Victor Reznov, Captain John “Soap” MacTavish, Captain John Price, Sergeant Foley (voiced by Keith David) and more of your favorite characters and Bronies in the game!

* Best Music Soundtracks - Scored by well-talented Hans Zimmer, best known to all your favorite movies, along with Xarahox the Piano and the songs from broke-back Nickelback including the internet remixes with splices and such! Including the newly-added soundtrack of “Space Oddity” done by David Bowie and cover-done by Lady Heroine and “F*** You, Texas” by Tom Mathis!

* All the Rage, All the Fun - Play endless time this game with all good times with epic drama, humor, and hilarious rage-quitting moments with cans.wav along the way with memes like Nyan Cat, Y U NO, U MAD BRO, and Ramirez Does Everything!

item.title: Rage comic: Grades - 2013
item.media:title: Rage comic: Grades - 2013
item.media:description:
It was the end of the year and I was thinking of the final exams - this came out of my head xD

In NZ we don't actually grade our work by "A+, A, A-, B+" etc. We grade it by "Not Achieved(F), Achieved(probably around C, C+?), Merit(maybe B+) and Excellence(A+)".


!!I don't own or take credit for Rage Comics!!

item.title: Rage Comic: Apple - 2013
item.media:title: Rage Comic: Apple - 2013
item.media:description:
I think 2013 was my big "meme phase". Y'know, Rage Comics, LOLcats, cringy sayings kids repeated way too much but was cool because the Internet did it and your parents never understood... that sort of thing.

I thought the idea was pretty cool to put Poppi in as an unofficial R.C. character. Plus I think this was the first time I experimented with "still" squash-and-stretch (panel 4) and it came out pretty successful.

!!I don't own or take credit for Rage Comics!!
